,"votes":2,"hasVoted":false},"comment":{"comments":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/15028/comment/30553","id":"30553","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mdlr","name":"mdlr","key":"mdlr","accountId":"557058:29fd1eba-b820-4c8d-9228-0f52cb260d76","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Michael De La Rue","active":false,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"body":"I traced the full shutdown process;  the point at which the shutdown locks up is whilst running *K99lvm2-monitor*.  \r\n\r\nattached file strace-of-vgs-during-shutdown-public.png shows strace running against that process.\r\n\r\nIt seems that it needs multiple long (multiminute) timeouts for every single loopback device.  ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mdlr","name":"mdlr","key":"mdlr","accountId":"557058:29fd1eba-b820-4c8d-9228-0f52cb260d76","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Michael De La Rue","active":false,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"created":"2012-08-03T03:10:32.630-0500","updated":"2012-08-03T03:10:32.630-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/15028/comment/30554","id":"30554","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mdlr","name":"mdlr","key":"mdlr","accountId":"557058:29fd1eba-b820-4c8d-9228-0f52cb260d76","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Michael De La Rue","active":false,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"body":"Looking at the Red Hat rc scripts, (/etc/rc.d/init.d/netfs) they take the responsibility to delete loopbacks which have been created due to local file mounts.  They do not attempt to delete other loopbacks.  I'm not even sure that there is a clear way for Red Hat to do that.  \n\nMy feeling is that there are two possibilities\n\na) the storage controller services from eucalyptus-cloud delete all of the tgtd associations and then delete the loopbacks during shutdown\n\nb) a new script is added before K05eucalyptus-cloud and before K75netfs which does something like \n\n{code}\nfor i in `losetup --all | grep /var/lib/eucalyptus/volumes  | sed 's/:.*//'`; do losetup -d $i; done`\n{code}\n\n\na) sort of seems like a right thing to do but\nb) is safer since it will also delete loopbacks which get forgotten about due to application inconsistency etc.  \n\nIt might even be a good idea to do both.  \n\n\nN.B. With the shutdown running all night, only about 11 of 100 loopbacks have been processed;  This likely means that shutting down a system will take about a week :-) ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mdlr","name":"mdlr","key":"mdlr","accountId":"557058:29fd1eba-b820-4c8d-9228-0f52cb260d76","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/15f3c4b7a0cf758ddb400a37f09f0c86?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26avatarId%3D10122%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Michael De La Rue","active":false,"timeZone":"Europe/Berlin"},"created":"2012-08-03T03:23:19.197-0500","updated":"2012-08-03T03:23:19.197-0500"},{"self":"h